    <arm_group_type>Experimental</arm_group_type>
    <description>Rivaroxaban will be provided according to an age- and body weight-adjusted dosing schedule to achieve a similar exposure in children as that observed in adults treated for VTE (venous thromboembolism) with 20 mg rivaroxaban daily. Rivaroxaban will be provided as a tablet for children 12 to 18 years. Once the age-and body weight-adjusted dosing regimen has been finally confirmed for the age group 6 to &lt; 12 years, rivaroxaban will be provided as tablets (and subsequently as oral suspension) for this age group.</description>
  </arm_group>
